@Marcelo-Theodoro 
Yep that should include python 3.6 which is supported by Lambda, we just missed this reference when we updated all the docs.

@jrowen 
CodeBuild does not have a supported python 3.6 image. As of the time of this writing they have 3.5.2 as their most recent version, so our CloudFormation template cannot generate a build environment for a python 3.6 project right now.

If you use the `chalice deploy` process you are uploading to straight to Lambda, there is no reason to use a python 3.5 environment rather than a 3.6 environment which will match the lambda runtime exactly. So the error and warning are both correct.

