After sleeping on it, I think we'll want to try out both applications (the mean daily return, and the CAGR approach) to see what feels the most correct.  I'm a bit torn now that I think about it. Since the cone is calculated _everyday_ for application of risk monitoring in more or less _real-time_ I feel like we should be using the simple mean returns.  As I see it we have 2 approaches  up for debate for drawing the slop of the line that bisects the cone which are dependent on choosing how to compute the _OOS daily return_ projection. So should the daily return be computed as:

a)  mean(backtest_daily_returns)
b) (1 + backtest_CAGR)^(1/252) - 1 

