@kotfu 
I believe the unicode issue is solved if you set ``shlex.whitespace_split`` to True. Otherwise anything not in ``wordchars`` gets split into an individual token. So something like 'αβγδ' would become ['α', 'β', 'γ', 'δ']

Is there a danger in just having ``shlex`` split on whitespace to allow unicode support? We can always handle the punctuation characters like I did in ``tokens_for_completion()``. Plus the ``punctuation_chars`` argument to ``shlex`` wasn't added until 3.6 so I'm not sure if we can use it anyway.

